# Code Standards — web_app

## JavaScript/TypeScript
- Use TypeScript for all code; prefer `interface` over `type`
- Avoid `enum`; use maps or union literals
- Use `function` keyword for pure functions; omit semicolons
- RORO pattern: receive object args, return object
- Avoid unnecessary curly braces in conditionals; single-line if without braces

```ts
interface FetchUserArgs { id: string }
interface FetchUserResult { user: User | null }

export function fetchUser({ id }: FetchUserArgs): FetchUserResult {
  if (!id) return { user: null }
  const user = cache.get(id)
  if (user) return { user }
  return { user: null }
}
```

## Naming
- Variables with auxiliaries: `isLoading`, `hasError`, `shouldFetch`
- Directories/files kebab-case
- Named exports for components and helpers

## File structure (per component)
- Exported component
- Subcomponents
- Helpers
- Static content
- Types/interfaces at file end
